		<div class="postbody">
			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Anyone well-versed with mental health and how to approach a situation?
				</h2>
				

						
							
							
							
						
						
				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1769047">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							So, I have a member of chosen family (not an actual blood relative, just someone I decided to include in my definition of &quot;family&quot; many years ago) who has suddenly, spontaneously become very vitriolic to the point of berating everyone and everything around her, including my kid.<br />
<br />
In over a decade of knowing this person I have seen plenty of passive-aggressive behavior and learned to just not trigger ire while around said person but recently over the holidays things flared up when we met briefly on the holiday route to see people for various  celebrations and after the outburst I spoke to others who have known her longer than I have.<br />
<br />
Apparently she has a history of getting really pissed off and throwing tantrums and when confronted with any sort of logic she just changes the subject and attacks from a different angle.<br />
<br />
She has heavy expectations about how things should be, but refuses to communicate them, then later accuses people of not understanding and the cycle of berating begins again.<br />
<br />
I'm a pretty big outsider in this but my main question is, how do I do anything as a parent of a child and not make things worse for my child with regards to this person?<br />
<br />
I don't have any idea what causes this sort of behaviour mentally.<br />
<br />
This person is not on drugs, does not drink (adamantly hates both, in fact) and came out the other side of menopause almost 15 years ago (so probably not hormonal, although I was told by someone else that she got REALLY bad the same way around that time for a few years).<br />
<br />
Clearly something is extra wrong here because for a long period of time I was speaking to her somewhat regularly over the phone and showing up for multiple holidays for years, but things just flipped and she started saying horrible things to EVERYONE, not just anyone she was upset at.<br />
<br />
Any ideas?<br />
<br />
I know it's not much to go off of, but I have more, I just don't know what's relevant.<br />
<br />
(edit --<br />
I really want to find a way to do something about this without upsetting the emotional teacup ride.<br />
Before this turn of events, I really enjoyed spending time with this person.<br />
)
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
