							Ideally, you want to maintain your composure and defuse the situation. If she is bi-polar, she likely won't listen to reason in that moment anyway so you may need to just let her have her tantrum but maintain your composure during it.  If you find yourself losing your cool, don't be afraid to leave the room and distance yourself from it so you don't lose your cool. If you are followed, then explain that you respect them but need some time to digest what was said and would appreciate some space so you can do that.  As for passive aggressive statements, I find it best to not respond to them.
