							This may not be relevant to this situation, but one of the most therapeutic experiences I ever had was the first time I tried x in the form of a molly.  I did it with my roommates and one roommate &amp; I at the time were not getting along very well.   That night we were able to say absolutely anything we wanted to each other and the molly made so that everything was said and received with love.  Since then we get along great, our friendship went from a 3 to a 9 (outa 10).  I have also heard that rolling a molly has done wonders for PTSD, considering my experience I think this 100% true.  This is something I think everyone should know considering that returned military suicidal rates are very high right now.    <br />
<br />
<br />
My stance about x is that I would enjoy doing it maybe once a year recreational.  I don't advocate any level of abuse. I do highly recommend that shrinks get the ability to prescribe x in a controlled environment for therapy.  That will never happen because if you can accomplish so much positive therapy and maybe even resolve signification issues, then the prama companies want noting to do with it and will suppress it.
