			<div class="postrow">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Anyone well-versed with mental health and how to approach a situation?
				</h2>
				

						
						
							
						
				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1769252">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							It seems to me that there exists two responses depending on how strongly you value the relationship and how valuable that person is compared to other relationships and potential new ones.  <br />
<br />
Response 1:  remove her from your life.  She is presently negative to both yourself and harmful for the minor.  <br />
Response 2:  she previously was a valuable relationship despite her potential illness.  As you say the overt negativity directed toward you is a change.  Ask why the change has occurred.  Find a solution to that change.  If no solution exists such that the previous state could be returned to then end ties with her.  <br />
<br />
Option 2 is the more precarious and less probable positive outcome.  However if you value the past relationship more than the additional investment will incur times the probility of a successful resolution then do that. I'm assuming you do not value helping the mentally ill intrinsically though.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
